#ROOM
Vnum     12501
Name     &OThe Road from Elwynn&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The lush green trees of Elwynn Forest abruptly end here, giving way to
the dry, golden plains of Westfall. The wind picks up, carrying a fine
layer of dust. To the west, the road continues into the heart of the
abandoned farmlands.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12502
Desc      The road continues toward a neglected farm.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12090
Desc      The tree line of Elwynn Forest.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12502
Name     &OFurlbrow's Pumpkin Patch&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A dilapidated wagon sits by the side of the road. The pumpkin patch here
is overgrown with weeds, and the scarecrows look unnervingly sinister in
the dry wind. The Furlbrows were forced out by the Defias long ago.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12501
Desc      The road back to Elwynn Forest.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12503
Desc      The dusty plains stretch out before you.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset O 0 12509 1 12502
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12503
Name     &OThe Dust Plains&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The golden grass of Westfall is parched and brittle. The wind howls
across the open plains, kicking up small dust devils. Great Goretusks
root through the hard earth here, searching for scraps.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12502
Desc      Furlbrow's Pumpkin Patch.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12506
Desc      The plains continue south.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12504
Desc      The fields of Saldean's Farm.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12507 2 12503
  Reset G 1 12502 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12504
Name     &OSaldean's Farm - The Fields&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The wheat here is dead and rotting on the stalk. Massive mechanical
Harvest Watchers patrol the fields erratically, their gears grinding
as they attack anything that moves. 
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12503
Desc      The Dust Plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12505
Desc      The Saldean farmhouse.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12505 2 12504
  Reset G 1 12503 10
Reset O 0 12513 3 12504
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12505
Name     &OSaldean's Farmhouse&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     One of the few farmhouses in Westfall that hasn't been burned to the
ground. It is sturdy but shows signs of recent attacks. The smell of
hearty stew fills the room, offering a rare comfort in this harsh land.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12504
Desc      The fields outside.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12509 1 12505
  Reset E 1 12510 10 16
Reset M 0 12510 1 12505
Reset O 0 12501 2 12505
Reset O 0 12511 1 12505
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12506
Name     &OThe Dust Plains - South&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The road becomes deeply rutted here from the passage of heavy carts.
To the west, a large, fortified hill rises above the plains. You can
see the banners of the People's Militia snapping in the wind.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12503
Desc      The northern plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12507
Desc      The base of Sentinel Hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12528
Desc      A dusty path leading toward a gnoll camp.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12507 1 12506
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12507
Name     &OBase of Sentinel Hill&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     You stand at the foot of the only safe haven in Westfall. Makeshift
barricades of sharpened logs and overturned wagons line the path leading
up the hill. Militia recruits practice their spear thrusts nearby.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12506
Desc      The Dust Plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    12508
Desc      The path winds up to the tower.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12508
Name     &OSentinel Hill - Tower&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A sturdy stone tower stands at the peak of the hill, offering a commanding
view of the entire zone. Gryan Stoutmantle stands here, shouting orders
and organizing the resistance against the Defias Brotherhood.
~
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    12507
Desc      The base of the hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12509
Desc      The militia barracks.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12510
Desc      The militia encampment.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12501 1 12508
  Reset E 1 12505 10 11
  Reset G 1 12506 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12509
Name     &OSentinel Hill - Barracks&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A large wooden building serving as the command center and sleeping
quarters for the People's Militia. Maps of Defias movements are pinned
to the walls. Captain Danuvin looks over the rosters with a grim face.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12508
Desc      The tower outside.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12502 1 12509
  Reset E 1 12515 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12510
Name     &OSentinel Hill - Encampment&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Tents are clustered tightly together here for warmth and protection.
Wounded soldiers rest on cots, and the smell of woodsmoke is thick.
From here, the road continues southwest toward the Dagger Hills.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12508
Desc      The tower.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction southwest~
ToRoom    12513
Desc      The road to the Dagger Hills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12511
Desc      The Dead Acre.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12511
Name     &OThe Dead Acre - North&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A massive, abandoned farm that has completely fallen to ruin. The soil
here is dead, and the mechanical Harvest Watchers have completely taken
over. It is a dangerous place to wander alone.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12510
Desc      Sentinel Hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12512
Desc      Deeper into the Dead Acre.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12505 2 12511
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12512
Name     &OThe Dead Acre - South&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The wreckage of a windmill groans in the wind. Huge Fleshripper birds
circle overhead, waiting for the mechanical golems to finish off any
foolish travelers.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12511
Desc      The northern edge of the farm.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12508 2 12512
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12513
Name     &OThe Dagger Hills&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The terrain becomes rugged and rocky here. The hills provide perfect
cover for Defias Trappers, who hide in the scrub brush waiting to ambush
caravans. The road winds its way south toward the town of Moonbrook.
~
#EXIT
Direction northeast~
ToRoom    12510
Desc      The safety of Sentinel Hill.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12514
Desc      The outskirts of Moonbrook.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12504 2 12513
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12514
Name     &OMoonbrook - Outskirts&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand at the edge of Moonbrook. Once a thriving agricultural hub, it
has been completely taken over by the Defias Brotherhood. Pillagers and
looters roam the streets freely. The buildings are burned and heavily
damaged.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12513
Desc      The Dagger Hills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12515
Desc      The ruined inn.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    12516
Desc      The center of town.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12503 1 12514
  Reset E 1 12512 10 5
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12515
Name     &OMoonbrook - Ruined Inn&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The roof of the inn has caved in, and the bar is smashed to splinters.
Defias thugs use this place as a hideout. The walls are scorched black
from the fire magic of the Pillagers.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12514
Desc      The outskirts of town.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12503 1 12515
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12516
Name     &OMoonbrook - Town Center&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The town square is a mess of broken carts and looted goods. Defias Looter
scavenge whatever they can find. To the east stands a large, ominously
intact barn that the Brotherhood heavily guards.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    12514
Desc      The outskirts of town.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12517
Desc      The Old Barn.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 12512 2 12516
  Reset E 1 12504 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12517
Name     &OMoonbrook - The Old Barn&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The interior of this barn is hiding a massive secret. The floorboards
have been pulled up, revealing a dark, spiraling tunnel leading deep into
the earth. This is the secret entrance to the Defias Brotherhood's
underground stronghold.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    12516
Desc      The town center.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    12900
Desc      The tunnel leads down into The Deadmines.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     12518
Name     &OThe Dust Plains - West&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     Heading west from Sentinel Hill, the plains stretch out toward the
ocean. The wind is incredibly fierce here, frequently whipping up
violent, sentient Dust Devils that batter everything in their path.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    12510
